headline: Why MSCI (MSCI) Stock Is Down Today
summary: Shares of investment analytics provider MSCI (NYSE:MSCI) fell 2.6% in the afternoon session after the major indices continued to retreat (Nasdaq -1.5%, S&P 500 -1.2%) amid profit-taking and renewed concerns about tariffs.
